"|  Option  |  Description                   |\n"
"|----------|--------------------------------|\n"
"| `-f`     | Display the FQDN               |\n"
"| `-i`     | Display the system IPs address |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:177
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Tip\n"
"    This command is used by various network programs to identify the machine.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:179
msgid ""
"To assign a host name, it is possible to use the `hostname` command, but the "
"changes will not be retained at the next boot. The command with no arguments "
"displays the host name."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:181
msgid ""
"To set the host name, the file `/etc/sysconfig/network` must be modified:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:186
msgid "``` NETWORKING=yes HOSTNAME=pc-rocky.mondomaine.lan ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:188
msgid ""
"The RedHat boot script also consults the `/etc/hosts` file to resolve the "
"host name of the system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:190
msgid ""
"When the system boots, Linux evaluates the `HOSTNAME` value in the `/etc/"
"sysconfig/network` file."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:192
msgid ""
"It then uses the `/etc/hosts` file to evaluate the main IP address of the "
"server and its host name. It deduces the DNS domain name."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:194
msgid ""
"It is therefore essential to fill in these two files before any "
"configuration of network services."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:197
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Tip\n"
