#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:292
msgid "## DHCP configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:294
msgid ""
"The **DHCP** protocol (**D**ynamic **H**ost **C**Control **P**rotocol) "
"allows you to obtain a complete IP configuration via the network. This is "
"the default configuration mode of a network interface under Rocky Linux, "
"which explains why a system connected to the network of an Internet router "
"can function without additional configuration."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:296
msgid ""
"The configuration of interfaces under Rocky Linux is done in the `/etc/"
"sysconfig/network-scripts/` folder."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:298
msgid ""
"For each Ethernet interface, a `ifcfg-ethX` file allows for the "
"configuration of the associated interface."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:305
msgid "``` DEVICE=eth0 ONBOOT=yes BOOTPROTO=dhcp HWADDR=00:0c:29:96:32:e3 ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '*  '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:307
msgid "Interface name : (must be in the file name)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:311
msgid "``` DEVICE=eth0 ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:313
msgid "Automatically start the interface:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:317
msgid "``` ONBOOT=yes ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:319
msgid "Make a DHCP request when the interface starts up:"
