#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:454
msgid "## Troubleshooting"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:456
msgid ""
"The `ping` command sends datagrams to another machine and waits for a "
"response."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:458
msgid ""
"It is the basic command for testing the network because it checks the "
"connectivity between your network interface and another."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:460
msgid "Syntax of the `ping` command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:464
msgid "``` ping [-c numerical] destination ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:466
msgid ""
"The `-c` (count) option allows you to stop the command after the countdown "
"in seconds."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:472
msgid "``` [root]# ping âc 4 localhost ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:475
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Tip\n"
"    Validate connectivity from near to far\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1) '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:477
msgid "Validate the TCP/IP software layer"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:481
msgid "``` [root]# ping localhost ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:483
msgid ""
"\"Pinging\" the inner loop does not detect a hardware failure on the network "
"interface. It simply determines whether the IP software configuration is "
"correct."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '2) '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:485
msgid "Validate the network card"
