#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:559
msgid "### `ipcalc` command"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:561
msgid ""
"The `ipcalc` (**ip calculation**) command is used to calculate the address "
"of a network or broadcast from an IP address and a mask."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:563
msgid "Syntax of the `ipcalc` command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:567
msgid "``` ipcalc [options] IP <netmask> ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:574
msgid ""
"``` [root]# ipcalc âb 172.16.66.203 255.255.240.0 BROADCAST=172.16.79.255 ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:577
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Tip\n"
"    This command is interesting followed by a redirection to automatically fill in the configuration files of your interfaces:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:581
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    ```\n"
"    [root]# ipcalc âb 172.16.66.203 255.255.240.0 >> /etc/sysconfig/network-scripts/ifcfg-eth0\n"
"    ```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:586
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"|  Option  |  Description                           |\n"
"|----------|----------------------------------------|\n"
"|  `-b`    | Displays the broadcast address.        |\n"
"|  `-n`    | Displays the network address and mask. |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:588
msgid ""
"`ipcalc` is a simple way to calculate the IP information of a host. The "
"various options indicate what information `ipcalc` should display on the "
"standard output. Multiple options can be specified. An IP address on which "
"to operate must be specified. Most operations also require a network mask or "
"CIDR prefix."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:597
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Option short | Option long | Description                                                                  |\n"
"|---------------|---------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------|\n"
"| `-b`          | `--broadcast` | Displays the broadcast address of the given IP address and the network mask. |\n"
"| `-h`          | `--hostname`  | Displays the hostname of the IP address given via DNS.                       |\n"
"| `-n`          | `--netmask`   | Calculates the network mask for the given IP address. Assumes that the IP address is part of a complete class A, B, or C network. Many networks do not use default network masks, in which case an incorrect incorrect value will be returned. |\n"
"| `-p`          | `--prefix`    | Indicates the prefix of the mask/IP address.                                 |\n"
"| `-n`          | `--network`   | Indicates the network address of the given IP address and mask.              |\n"
"| `-s`          | `--silent`    | Never displays any error messages.                                           |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:599
msgid "### `ss` command"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:601
msgid ""
"The `ss` (**socket statistics**) command displays the listening ports on the "
"network."
