#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:640
msgid "### IP or MAC address conflicts"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:642
msgid ""
"A misconfiguration can cause multiple interfaces to use the same IP address. "
"This can happen when a network has multiple DHCP servers or when the same IP "
"address is manually assigned multiple times."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:644
msgid ""
"When the network is malfunctioning, and when an IP address conflict could be "
"the cause, it is possible to use the `arp-scan` software (requires the EPEL "
"repository):"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:648
msgid "``` $ dnf install arp-scan ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:653
msgid "``` $ arp-scan -I eth0 -l"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:664
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"172.16.1.104  00:01:02:03:04:05       3COM CORPORATION\n"
"172.16.1.107  00:0c:29:1b:eb:97       VMware, Inc.\n"
"172.16.1.250  00:26:ab:b1:b7:f6       (Unknown)\n"
"172.16.1.252  00:50:56:a9:6a:ed       VMWare, Inc.\n"
"172.16.1.253  00:50:56:b6:78:ec       VMWare, Inc.\n"
"172.16.1.253  00:50:56:b6:78:ec       VMWare, Inc. (DUP: 2)\n"
"172.16.1.253  00:50:56:b6:78:ec       VMWare, Inc. (DUP: 3)\n"
"172.16.1.253  00:50:56:b6:78:ec       VMWare, Inc. (DUP: 4)\n"
"172.16.1.232   88:51:fb:5e:fa:b3       (Unknown) (DUP: 2)\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:667
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Tip\n"
"    As the above example shows, it is also possible to have MAC address conflicts! These problems are brought about by virtualization technologies and the copying of virtual machines.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:669
msgid "## Hot configuration"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:671
msgid "The `ip` command can hot add an IP address to an interface"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:675
msgid "``` ip addr add @IP dev DEVICE ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:681
msgid "``` [root]# ip addr add 192.168.2.10 dev eth1 ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:683
msgid ""
"The `ip` command allows for the activation or deactivation of an interface:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:688
msgid "``` ip link set DEVICE up ip link set DEVICE down ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:695
msgid "``` [root]# ip link set eth1 up [root]# ip link set eth1 down ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:697
msgid "The `ip` command is used to add a route:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:701
msgid "``` ip route add [default|netaddr] via @IP [dev device] ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/12-network.md:708
msgid ""
"``` [root]# ip route add default via 192.168.1.254 [root]# ip route add "
"192.168.100.0/24 via 192.168.2.254 dev eth1 ```"
msgstr ""

